This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump at the swearing-in ceremony of Gina Haspel as the new Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA). The President praises Haspel's qualifications and highlights her long career in the CIA, including her role in the fight against al Qaeda. He also commends her for being the first woman to lead the CIA. Haspel then speaks, expressing her gratitude for the President's confidence in her and her commitment to the agency and its mission. She also emphasizes the need for continued improvement and innovation within the agency to address the challenges and threats faced by the nation.